article.headline: Delaware 72, American 63
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP)-- David Lunn hit eight free throws in the final minute to help Delaware survive a late American rally and secure a 72-63 win Tuesday night. Lunn, who finished with 15 points, also came up with a steal for Delaware (2-0) with 20 seconds to play and the Blue Hens protecting a 66-61 lead. Lunn was fouled and made both free throws to push the lead back to seven, ending any chance for an American comeback. The Blue Hens led by as many as 15 points in the second half. But American (0-2) turned the ball over just four times in the second half and twice trimmed the lead to three in the final two minutes. American's Andres Rodriguez, who finished with 13 points, made a layup with 43.6 seconds to play to bring the score to 64-61 before Lunn put the game away at the free-throw line. Jernavis Draughn scored 16 to lead the Eagles, who started slowly for the second straight game, trailing 41-28 at halftime. That was a considerable improvement over American's eight first-half points in Saturday's season-opening loss at Maryland. Mike Ames scored 12 of his 16 in the first half to lead the fast start for the Blue Hens. <
